# oh-my-colab Core Rules

## Session Start
Read .ohc/notepad.md for current working state.
Read .ohc/PROJECT.md for project context.
If the repo root has **CONTEXT.md** or **CONTEXT-MAP.md** (`ohc setup` optional glossary), skim for domain vocabulary before implementation work.
Greet user: current task + git branch + plan progress.

## Workflow Routing
Match **`hooks/keyword-map.json`** so Cursor behavior aligns with Claude Code hooks.

- "explore"   → EXPLORE
- "plan this", "design this", "write a plan" … → PLAN (confirm before BUILD)
- "build" / "implement" → BUILD
- "review" … → REVIEW
- "ship" / "ship it" / "finish branch" → SHIP
- "retro" → RETRO
- "autopilot" / "full auto" → chained PLAN+BUILD+REVIEW per map
- "ralph", `/ohc-ralph`, "keep going" → persistent BUILD (see **`skills/ralph`**)
- document-intake phrases + `/ohc-document-intake` → **`skills/document-intake`**
- "caveman mode" / exit phrases → **`skills/caveman`**
- "team", `/ohc-team` → parallel workers + RESULT.json gate
- `/ohc-research`, "research …" → `.ohc/research/` cache first

### Cursor MCP
Some MCPs (**context7**, **figma**, **sentry**) are often enabled via **[Cursor dashboard / plugins](https://cursor.com/dashboard/plugins)**. `ohc setup` may omit them from `.cursor/mcp.json` for stability — follow setup’s post-install tip if shown.

## Discipline Rules
- No code for tasks >30min without a plan in .ohc/plans/
- Always run tests before claiming done — read the actual output
- Stay within agreed scope. Spotted issues → .ohc/notepad.md, not fixes.
- Use Context7 for any external library docs. Check .ohc/research/ cache FIRST;
  only fetch on miss, then save back so future sessions reuse it.
- Run **`ohc doctor`** for workspace health hints.

## Memory Protocol
- After significant work: update .ohc/notepad.md (what done, what next, blockers)
- New project gotcha: append to .ohc/PROJECT.md Known Gotchas
- Novel pattern: write draft to .ohc/skills/ for RETRO to review

## Agent Routing
- planner (opus): design, requirements, decomposition
- executor (sonnet): code writing
- reviewer (opus): code review, security
- verifier (sonnet): test execution
- debugger (sonnet): root cause analysis
- researcher (haiku): Context7, Brave Search
- writer (haiku): changelogs, PR descriptions
- collaborator (sonnet): team handoffs
